stateDiagram-v2
    classDef okState fill:#dce7f2,stroke:#2e5f8a,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#1f2933
    classDef offState fill:#e8eaed,stroke:#6b7480,color:#1f2933

    state "CREATED" as CRE
    state "IN_PROGRESS" as PROG
    state "COMPLETED" as DONE
    state "FAILED" as FAIL
    state "EXPIRED" as EXP
    state "CANCELLED" as CAN

    [*] --> CRE : POST /auth/sessions —<br/>session for one auth-flow run<br/>(expires_at = now + 10 min)

    CRE --> PROG : first step submitted<br/>(POST .../steps/1)

    PROG --> DONE : last required step passed —<br/>JWT access token + rotating<br/>refresh token minted
    PROG --> FAIL : step max_attempts exceeded

    CRE --> EXP : step submitted<br/>after expires_at
    PROG --> EXP : step submitted<br/>after expires_at

    CRE --> CAN : user cancels (DELETE<br/>/auth/sessions/id)
    PROG --> CAN : user cancels

    DONE --> [*]
    FAIL --> [*]
    EXP --> [*]
    CAN --> [*]

    note left of PROG
        Retries of a failed attempt (below
        max_attempts) and advance to the next
        step both stay within IN_PROGRESS.
        Each step has its own status:
        PENDING, IN_PROGRESS, COMPLETED,
        FAILED, SKIPPED, DELEGATED —
        optional steps may be skipped.
    end note

    note right of CAN
        Terminal states are one-way:
        any further submission answers
        HTTP 409 (state conflict).
        Tokens are minted only on
        COMPLETED — never before
        the last step.
    end note

    class DONE okState
    class FAIL offState
    class EXP offState
    class CAN offState
